text: Chanced upon this jap stall during breakfast. Ordered their mee Siam. Surprisingly good. Very old school feel. Nice balance of sourness. Only thing lacking was no lime and gravy wasn’t hot enough thou it was in the soup pot but still it was good.

Saw this new japanese food stall at kallang estate market and decided to give it a try. Ordered chikin katsu curry rice and top up $1 for an omelette, order gyoza too...food is really good, satisfying dinner, will be back again to try others. 👍

Tried the yakitori don for $6. Chicken was really tender and flavour was on point.

Portion size is a little small for $6 . Maybe more value if it came with a small bowl of miso soup.

Will come back to try other dishes

Delicious Jap dinner @ Yoshiki Japanese Food  😊
First time finished up the whole bowl of yakitori don by myself.. it's so yummy...😁😋
If u really in desperate need of Japanese then u can try but for the price vs quantity i think there are better choices here.
